This track begins reasonably ok. Dua Lipa is a very average singer suitable for Pop, but the vocal style for the early part of the song is intriguing. Unfortunately the mundane and repetitive over powered beat is annoying, drowning out the basic rhythm guitar notes. When you think there is a great build into the chorus, it falls completely flat. This track had potential, a lost opportunity with writers playing too safe, to keep it too simplistic. Seriously vary the beats, not complete repetition and over powered. Bring out more of the musical element. It is poor, but this is typical commercial music, what do I expect. Rating 4/10

Out of expectations
It is very understandable why most people cannot get used to this kind of sound in Dua, because they are used to songs that are straight forward pop, and there is nothing wrong with it. Meanwhile, the last two songs released by Dua have many synth/psychadelic nuances, the music is particularized, there is a lot of attention to detail in creating a sound that is more raw, unlike everyday pop. Still, it's pop, but infused. I personally like it a lot, it's very rich, it has variation an unpredictable melody (here people sometimes feel uncomfortable, because actually good music, with alternative pop tendencies). I was surprised by someone who commented, no, she can do better... she has reinvented herself and the way she sounds after an album that spent years in the center of attention, with people saying she reinvebted retro/disco music!!!! Itâ€™s obvious that there's work, there's dedication, it's not super duper extra mainstream. Doesn't that tell you something? Her music is CURATED! It's a bop, and its quality!
